         <apex:outputPanel layout="none" rendered="{!$CurrentPage.parameters.type=='AF'}">
                 <div class="TermsConditionsText">
                                        <h1>Direct Energy Solar Affiliate Network Agreement</h1>
                <p class="intro">Once an Affiliate Candidate has completed the free, no obligation registration process and has been verified as a participant in the program, an addendum detailing payment amounts will be sent via email.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span>As an Direct Energy Solar Affiliate, the organization will take active steps to promote Direct Energy Solar to its constituents (members, visitors, citizens, etc.) including, but not limited to, providing a written endorsement of Direct Energy Solar, including the Direct Energy Solar offer on the organization&rsquo;s official website, newsletters, e-newsletters, and social media vehicles, and posting of flyers in appropriate areas.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Affiliate Organization must have 100 or more constituents to qualify for this program.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Each time a properly-registered constituent signs a contract for solar services with Direct Energy Solar, the Affiliate will receive an established Direct Energy Solar Affiliate program payment as a donation.</span></li>
                    <li><span>In lieu of receiving the entire Affiliate program payment, the Affiliate may elect to split the reward 50/50 with the constituent, passing along half of the amount as a referral discount. </span></li>
                    <li><span>A customer may only receive one referral discount per system.</span></li>
                    <li><span>In order for the constituent and/or Affiliate to receive their applicable discount and donation, the constituent&rsquo;s lead information must be properly registered with Direct Energy Solar in one of the following ways:</span></li>
                    <div class="subList">
                        <ul>
                            <li><span>Register on a co-branded landing page, provided by Direct Energy Solar</span></li>
                            <li><span>Register via the lead entry form on the Affiliate web portal</span></li>
                            <li><span>Contact Direct Energy Solar directly and cite the Affiliate Code, provided by Direct Energy Solar, during the first contact</span></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <li><span>When a constituent becomes a Direct Energy Solar customer and helps spread the word within the Affiliate organization, he/she can qualify for a separate appreciation payment in addition to the amount(s) paid to the constituent and/or Affiliate. In order to receive the separate appreciation reward, the referring constituent&rsquo;s name must be cited at the time of lead registration.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Constituents who have already established contact with Direct Energy Solar are considered duplicate leads and are not eligible for the Affiliate payment/discount structure.</span></li>
                    <li><span>All work for the solar power system sold will be performed by Direct Energy Solar.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Affiliate agrees to hold the terms of the agreement confidential, including payment amounts.</span></li>  
                    <li><span>Affiliate agrees to only utilize marketing materials approved by Direct Energy Solar when promoting the program and to perform no marketing or advertising activities without the express permission of Direct Energy Solar.</span></li>
                    <li><span>This agreement can be terminated at anytime by either party with a written notification. Referral Partner will get paid for any Qualified Leads referred prior to the date of cancellation.</span></li>
                </ul>
<p>By accepting this agreement, you acknowledge and agree to the terms and conditions above. You also confirm that you are an authorized representative of a qualifying non-profit or membership-based organization.</p>
