                                        <h1>Direct Energy Solar Corporate Affinity Agreement</h1>
                <p class="intro">Once a Corporate Affinity Partner Candidate has completed the free, no obligation registration process and has been verified as a participant in the program, an addendum detailing payment amounts will be sent via email.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span>The registered Affinity Partner agrees to provide a written endorsement of Direct Energy Solar and incorporate Direct Energy Solar&rsquo;s offer to any existing corporate affinity/employee discount program. The Affinity partner also agrees to post a customized link, provided by Direct Energy Solar, on its affinity site, where applicable.</span></li>
                    <li><span>The corporation must have 100 or more employees to qualify for this program.</span></li>
                    <li><span>When a properly-registered employee lead from the Affinity Partner signs a contract for solar services with Direct Energy Solar, Direct Energy Solar will extend to them an established Affinity discount, provided as a credit on the first invoice if the employee purchases the system, or as a cash rebate if the employee enrolls in Direct Energy Solar&rsquo;s monthly payment program.</span></li>
                    <li><span>The employee discount amount is applied in addition to the current publicly-available promotional discount.</span></li>
                    <li><span>In order for the Affinity Partner&rsquo;s employee to receive the discount, the employee must be properly registered with Direct Energy Solar in one of the following ways:</span></li>
